definition.value: Abnormal level of metabolite or other abnormal analyte result in a stool test.
Any structural anomaly of the ear.
Any functional anomaly of the ear.
The course a disease typically takes from its onset, progression in time, and eventual resolution or death of the affected individual.
Any functional anomaly of the vocal cord.
A functional anomaly of the mouth (which is also known as the oral cavity).
Any structural anomaly of the mouth, which is also known as the oral cavity.
Any anomaly of a reflex, i.e., of an automatic response mediated by the nervous system (a reflex does not need the intervention of conscious thought to occur).
Any functional abnormality of the eyelid.
Any deviation from the activity of coagulation factor V.
A functional abnormality affecting one or more of the cranial nerves, which emerge directly from the brain stem.
An unintentional, oscillating to-and-fro muscle movement affecting the tongue.
Any deviation from the normal concentration of urea nitrogen in the blood.
Any deviation from the normal concentration of a carboxylic acid in the urine.

This term groups terms representing abnormal findings derived from chest X-ray investigation of the lung. In general, lung abnormalities can manifest as opacities (areas of increased density) or as regions with decreased density.
An unintentional, oscillating to-and-fro muscle movement affecting the lip.
Abnormal appearance of material expectorated (coughed up) from the respiratory system and that is composed of mucus but may contain other substances such as pus, blood, microorganisms, and fibrin.
An anomaly of the adjacent structures (i.e., adnexa) of the eye, defined as the lacrimal apparatus, the extraocular muscles and the eyelids, eyelashes, eyebrows and the conjunctiva.
A functional anomaly of the adjacent structures (i.e., adnexa) of the eye, defined as the lacrimal apparatus, the extraocular muscles and the eyelids, eyelashes, eyebrows and the conjunctiva.
Underdevelopment of the carotid canal, which normally is a circular aperture in the temporal bone of the skull through which the internal carotid artery and the carotid plexus of nerves traverse.
Aplasia, that is failure to develop, of the fallopian tube.
Any functional abnormality of the part of the nervous system that consists of the nerves and ganglia outside of the brain and spinal cord.

label.value: Abnormal proportion of unswitched memory B cells
Decreased proportion of unswitched memory B cells

definition.value: A reduction below the normal proportion of non-class-switched memory B cells relative to the total number of B cells.
A reduction below the normal proportion of plasmablasts in circulation relative to total number of B cells.
An unusual infection classified by the affected body part.
A type of infection that is regarded as a sign of a pathological susceptibility to infection because of unusual severity or intensity of the infection.
An abnormal level of an analyte measured in the blood.

label.value: Decreased proportion of CD4-positive T cells

definition.value: A reduction in the proportion of CD4-positive T cells relative to the total number of T cells.
Any deviation from the normal concentration of a metabolite in a tissue.

An abnormality in the function of the chemical reactions related to processes including conversion of food to enter, synthesis of proteins, lipids, nucleic acids, and carbohydrates, or the elimination of waste products.
Any deviation from the normal cell count per volume of granulocytes in the blood circulation.
An abnormally reduced concentration of corticosterone in the blood.
